  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6597.86 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-9B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+15.2B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but approaching the critical flip zone. The massive +15.2B gamma wall at 6605 will trigger heavy dealer selling if breached, while a drop below 6590 puts dealers into buy-the-dip mode as negative gamma forces them to chase momentum lower. The GEX surge event combined with the tight 15-point range between max neg/pos gamma levels creates a high-tension setup where small moves will trigger outsized dealer responses.\n\nKey levels: 6605 resistance (dealer selling kicks in), 6590 support (dealer buying accelerates), and 6674 regime flip strike above which all bets are off.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile ping-ponging between 6590-6605 with explosive moves if either level breaks.",
